se update this with the earliest version of support.\">(Yes)</span></td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"Veja também","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/pt-BR/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/pop\"><code>Array.prototype.pop()</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/pt-BR/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/shift\"><code>Array.prototype.shift()</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/pt-BR/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/unshift\"><code>Array.prototype.unshift()</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/pt-BR/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/concat\"><code>Array.prototype.concat()</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Resumo","id":"summary"},{"text":"Exemplos","id":"examples"},{"text":"Especificações","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Compatibilidade em navegadores","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"Veja também","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"O método push() adiciona um ou mais elementos ao final de um array e retorna o novo comprimento desse array.","popularity":0.0053,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Array.prototype.push()","locale":"de","native":"Deutsch"},{"title":"Array.prototype.push()","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"Array.prototype.push()","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"Array.prototype.push()","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"Array.prototype.push()","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"Array.prototype.push()","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"Array.prototype.push()","locale":"pl","native":"Polski"},{"title":"Array.prototype.push()","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"Array.prototype.push()","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"},{"title":"Array.prototype.push()","locale":"zh-TW","native":"正體中文 (繁體)"}],"source":{"folder":"pt-br/web/javascript/reference/global_objects/array/push","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/